episodes.name: Winner Winner, Chicken Dinner
episodes.overview: The Tournament of All Stars kicks off with the first of three brackets! For this premiere challenge, the 6 Queens of Bracket 1 deliver head-banging heavy metal realness in an 80s-inspired music video.

episodes.name: Murder On The Dance Floor
episodes.overview: It's Week 2 of the first bracket, and the queens must make the judges drop dead with their improv performances in the whodunit, "Murder on the Dance Floor." Emmy award winning actor and red carpet darling, Colman Domingo, guest judges.

episodes.name: Hoop Queens Makeover
episodes.overview: It's a buzzer beater to the Semi Finals for this first bracket of queens as they scramble to makeover collegiate basketball players. Meanwhile, the MVQ point system has the dolls calling, "foul," on their sisters. Kate Beckinsale joins the judges panel.

episodes.name: Eight Ball
episodes.overview: A new bracket of queens arrive in the werkroom where lines are drawn in the sand between competitors. A special delivery from Ru has queens creating dope looks from items found in giant 8-balls. Nightlife icon, Susanne Bartsch, returns to turn the party.

episodes.name: Rappin' Roast
episodes.overview: After a gaggy MVQ Points Ceremony, the queens are ready to create the ultimate diss track and battle each other in a Rappin' Roast. Supernova superstar Chappell Roan stops by to get a taste of the hot and spicy bars.

episodes.name: Starrbooty: The Rebooty
episodes.overview: With the semi-finals at stake, it's heroes versus villains, as the queens funk it up for a dyn-o-mite performance of the movie rusical, "Starrbooty: The Rebooty." Legendary producer and director, Adam Shankman, choreographs and guest judges.

episodes.name: Wicked Good
episodes.overview: The final bracket of 6 queens descend onto the Main Stage to stake their claim for the Drag Race Hall of Fame. Working in teams the queens must create good and wicked witch looks for the runway. Ariana Grande and Cynthia Erivo enchant on the judges panel.

episodes.name: Stagecooch
episodes.overview: Coached by country superstar, Orville Peck, the queens divide into dueling country trios to perform honky tonk anthems at the first annual Stagecooch Festival. Drag Race choreographer extraordinaire Jamal Sims returns to the judges panel.

episodes.name: The Golden Bitchelor
episodes.overview: Things get real after a tense MVQ Points Ceremony. With 3 semi-final spots up for grabs, the queens vie for love and laughs in "The Golden Bitchelor" with "Fire Island" star Zane Phillips. Sitcom pro Mayan Lopez returns to help decide who will move on.

episodes.name: Tournament of All Stars Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The divine 9 Semi-Finalists return, and Mama Ru cranks up the heat by challenging them to serve their best celeb impersonations in the Snatch Game! Sarah Michelle Gellar slays the judges panel - and one All Star is sent home.

episodes.name: Tournament of All Stars Talent Invitational
episodes.overview: The 8 Semi-Finalists showcase their most gag-worthy talents in hopes of earning a spot in the finale. Superstar actress Devery Jacobs joins the judges- and one All Star is sent packing.

episodes.name: Tournament of All Stars Smackdown for the Crown
episodes.overview: One All Star returns to the competition, and everything is on the line as the final 8 Queens lip sync for the crown! Which Queen will snatch victory and be the newest face in the Drag Race Hall of Fame?

name: Season 10
overview: Let the games begin! 18 returning queens compete in the first-ever Tournament of All Stars, battling through brackets to test their charisma, uniqueness, nerve & talent! But only one queen will claim $200,000 and a spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame.
